# Doey Performance Review — 2026-04-18

**Task:** 604 — Performance review across token efficiency, latency/throughput, coordination quality, correctness/waste, branch/git, and fresh-install integrity.
**Synthesis:** W5 (this document) consolidates partial reports from W1 (token + install), W2 (latency/throughput), W3 (coordination), W4 (correctness + branch).
**Status:** Report only — no fixes implemented. Follow-up tasks are proposed in the final section.

Source reports (append-only, retained):
- `.doey/reports/perf-review-20260418-w1-token-and-install.md`
- `.doey/scratch/perf-review-w2-latency.md`
- `.doey/reports/perf-review-20260418-W3-coordination.md`
- `.doey/reports/perf-review-20260418-w4.md`

---

## 1. Executive summary — top 5 findings by impact

| # | Finding | Severity | Source | Dimensions affected |
|---|---------|----------|--------|---------------------|
| 1 | `on-pre-tool-use.sh` is 1132 lines, runs synchronously on every tool call | P0 | W2·P0-2, W3·F16 | latency + token (slow acks) |
| 2 | Worker stop hook chain runs CI-grade `go build`/`go vet`/`bash -n` serially (8 hooks, 2014 lines) | P0 | W2·P0-1, P1-6 | latency + throughput |
| 3 | Coordinator prompts are bloated (Subtaskmaster 735, Taskmaster 521, Boss 416 lines) with heavy rule duplication | P0 | W1·F1.1, W3·F3, W2·P2-8 | token + first-token latency |
| 4 | Proof gate is syntactic only (`grep '^PROOF_TYPE:'`) — false-positive completions | P0 | W4·F-W4-1 | correctness / waste |
| 5 | Branch guard has gaps: blocks `checkout/switch/merge` but not `git branch <new>`, `git worktree add`, `git reset --hard origin/...` | P0 | W4·F-W4-8 | correctness / branch (see task 603) |

**Common root cause** across items 1–3: rules, guards, and verification logic were added defensively without a second pass to compress. The cost is paid on every turn, not once.

