## 3. Findings by dimension

### 3.1 Token efficiency (W1)

| ID | Finding | Severity |
|----|---------|----------|
| F1.1 | `agents/doey-subtaskmaster.md` (735 lines) is ~60% redundant — reactive/no-polling/kill-protection stated 5× | P0 |
| F1.2 | `agents/doey-taskmaster.md` has duplicate opening paragraph (lines 11 & 15); Boss has 60-line STATUS CHECK PROTOCOL it doesn't run | P1 |
| F1.3 | `on-pre-compact.sh` dumps 500–1000 lines to stdout (agent context) every compaction — overlays × 200 lines + msgs + crash files | P0 |
| F1.4 | `.claude/skills/doey-masterplan/SKILL.md` bloat (long examples shadowed by the template) | P2 |
| F1.5 | `MEMORY.md` indexes 1 of 8 `feedback_proof_*.md` files — memory sprawl, duplicate intent | P2 |
| F1.6 | Status / result JSON files re-read by Subtaskmaster on every wake cycle | P1 (overlap with W2·P1-3) |
| F1.7 | Pre-compact preserves recent file list but not active-task scope — compacted agents re-ask | P1 |
| F1.8 (anti-rec) | **Do not** shrink `on-pre-tool-use.sh` for tokens alone — it doesn't reach agent context. Shrink it for latency (W2·P0-2). | — |

### 3.2 Latency / throughput (W2)

| ID | Finding | Severity |
|----|---------|----------|
| P0-1 | Stop-hook chain runs `go build ./...` + `go vet ./...` + per-file `bash -n` serially (worst case 20–40s per stop); 8 stop hooks = 2014 shell LOC parsed per stop | P0 |
| P0-2 | `on-pre-tool-use.sh` hot-path: jq/python3 subprocess per call, 2× `git rev-parse`, awk/sed/tr pipeline even for `ls`, 10s heartbeat rewrite | P0 |
| P1-3 | `taskmaster-wait.sh` N+1 `doey-ctl task get` pattern + double task-scan pre/post sleep + `_check_stale_heartbeats` iterates twice | P1 |
| P1-4 | `doey_send_verified` 4-retry chain: 0.5→1.0→2.0 backoff, 800ms paste-settle, 3s BUSY poll even on first attempt | P1 |
| P1-5 | Coordination hops degrade to `sleep 60` when `inotifywait` missing (macOS default) | P1 |
| P1-6 | `stop-results.sh` internal verify steps are serial — easy parallelism win | P1 |
| P2-7 | No warm-worker pool — dynamic spawns pay full 5–15s boot cost | P2 |
| P2-8 | Prompt size ≈ first-token latency (cross-ref W1·F1.1) | P2 |
| P2-9 (anti-rec) | Keep the 3s Taskmaster self-trigger in `stop-status.sh:192-207` — prevents silent Taskmaster | — |

