| F-W4-5 | Under-spawn: multi-file refactors delegated to 1 worker (task 600 partial) | P2 |
| F-W4-6 | Task 600 status drift — marked in_progress while worker idle; stale-heartbeat not wired to re-dispatch | P1 |
| F-W4-7 | (bundled with task 603) Git push workflow: no per-worker branch convention | P1 |
| F-W4-8 | (bundled with task 603) Branch guard gaps: `git branch <new>`, `git worktree add`, `git reset --hard origin/...`, `git stash pop` over branch point | P0 |
| F-W4-9 | (bundled with task 603) No branch-cleanup sweep after merged PRs | P2 |
| F-W4-10 | Duplicate task detection uses title-substring only — semantic duplicates pass through | P2 |

### 3.5 Fresh-install / install integrity (W1·§6)

| ID | Finding | Severity |
|----|---------|----------|
| F6.1 | `install.sh:331-335` skips writing `$HOME/.claude/doey/repo-path` for `/tmp` installs — `on-pre-tool-use.sh:30-44` self-repair then fails on fresh curl‑bash users | P0 |
| F6.2 | `on-pre-tool-use.sh` role-resolution 3-tier fallback masks a misconfigured install (silent "assume Worker") | P1 |
| F6.3 | `settings.json` entries are user-local; any new skill/hook that forgets to add them breaks fresh install | P1 |
| F6.4 | `expand-templates.sh` not run during install — templates ship unrendered if a dev commits the tmpl but forgets the .md | P1 |
| F6.5 | `doey doctor` does not check for `inotify-tools`/`fswatch` — install passes on macOS but hops are slow (cross-ref W2·P1-5) | P2 |
| F6.6 | Memory dir layout (`~/.claude/projects/...`) is not created by install — depends on Claude Code auto-init | P2 |

---

## 4. Conflict reconciliation

**`on-pre-tool-use.sh` size.** W1·F1.8 says *do not shrink for tokens* (this hook output does not reach agent context). W2·P0-2 and W3·F16 say *do shrink for latency* (runs synchronously per tool call). **Resolution:** shrink it, but optimize for hot-path wall-time (early-exit non-Bash tools, cache pane resolution, cheap VCS pre-filter) — not for byte count. This is captured in follow-up task #2.

**Worker spawn policy.** W4·F-W4-4 (over-spawn) and W4·F-W4-5 (under-spawn) pull in opposite directions. **Resolution:** both point at the same root cause — the dispatcher lacks a file-count/scope heuristic. Fix once (follow-up task #10), affects both.

---

